            All 11 tasks are complete. Here's a summary of the Windows/Git Bash support changes:

            ### Go CLI files (7 files)
            | File | Change |
            |------|--------|
            | [install.go](libs/cli/internal/install.go) | Added `binaryExt()` helper (`.exe` on Windows), guarded `chmod`, fixed `extractTarGz` matching |
            | [pluginloader.go](libs/cli/internal/pluginloader.go) | Appends `.exe` to plugin binary path on Windows |
            | [selfupdate.go](libs/cli/internal/selfupdate.go) | Uses `binaryExt()` for update loop + `extractTarGzAll`, guarded `chmod` |
            | [serve.go](libs/cli/internal/serve.go) | Uses `os.Interrupt` on Windows (vs `syscall.SIGINT/SIGTERM` on Unix) |
            | [pack.go](libs/cli/internal/pack.go) | Guarded `os.Chmod` on hook files for Windows |
            | [ide.go](libs/cli/internal/ide.go) | `filepath.ToSlash()` normalization for Continue.dev YAML paths on Windows |

            ### CI/Build files (3 files)
